briefdescription.para: Initialise the form, and create objects required for functionality. Contains event handlers for buttons and set the DrawingPanel image to the combined bitmap.

Defines behaviour when the enter/return key is pressed while the textbox is selected. If 'run' is entered it will run all of the commands displayed inside the left panel. If commands are entered it will display them within labels inside the panel.

parameterdescription.para: Object that raised the event, in this case TextBox
The event, in this case the Enter/Return key is pressed

briefdescription.para: Defines behaviour when the 'run' button is clicked. Parses the command and runs it before refreshing the bitmaps.

parameterdescription.para: Object that raised the event, in this case Run button
The event, in this case 'run' button clicked

briefdescription.para: Iterates through each label contained within the 'CommandPanel', parsing and running each line and refreshing the canvas.
Checks that commands are not clearing or infinitely running the program. Takes user input from the TextBox and adds each line to a label when called, directly below the previous label.

parameterdescription.para: Text entered by the user into the TextBox when the Enter/Return key is pressed

briefdescription.para: Loop through each label and add the lines to a List. SaveFileDialog prompts user to select a directory and saves to a directory in a text file when the user clicks 'OK' in the prompt.

parameterdescription.para: The object that raised the event, in this case the 'save' button
The event, in this case the 'save' button being clicked

briefdescription.para: Defines behaviour when the 'open' button is clicked. Calls a dialog box to select the file to open from a list of text files.

parameterdescription.para: The object that raised the event, in this case the 'open' button
The event, in this case the button being clicked

briefdescription.para: Event handler for the syntax button. Loops through user's code without affecting the bitmap, outputting any exceptions to the panel.
Outputs an error message to the rich text box displaying any errors when the user clicks the syntax button.

parameterdescription.para: The error message to show to the user
The line number that the error occured

briefdescription.para: Reset the program without needing to restart.
Required method for Designer support - do not modify the contents of this method with the code editor.
Clean up any resources being used.

parameterdescription.para: true if managed resources should be disposed; otherwise, false.

briefdescription.para: Create the form for the main application. Contains all the methods for UI functionality such as buttons and panels for displaying the drawing.
